quran[70]{c,v,t}:
  69,1,The Sure Reality
  69,2,What is the Sure Reality
  69,3,And what enables you to perceive what the Sure Reality is
  69,4,"The (tribes) of Thamud and ‘Ad denied the Sudden, Mighty Strike"
  69,5,Now as for the (tribe of) Thamud – they were destroyed by the overwhelming (catastrophe)
  69,6,"And the (tribe of) ‘Ad – they were destroyed with a furious, roaring windstorm"
  69,7,"Which God made to prevail against them for seven nights and eight days, uninterruptedly, so that you could have seen people lying overthrown in it, as though they were hollow trunks of palm-trees"
  69,8,Now do you see any of them remaining
  69,9,"And there was the Pharaoh, and many other communities before him, and the cities overthrown (where Lot’s people lived): all of them indulged in the unpardonable sins"
  69,10,"And they rebelled against their Lord’s Messenger (sent to each to warn them), and so He took hold of them with a severe seizing"
  69,11,"It was We Who, when the water (of the Flood in the time of Noah) burst beyond limits, carried you (i.e. your believing ancestors) in the on-moving Ark"
  69,12,"So that We might make it a reminder for you (to be transmitted from generation to generation), and that heeding ears might take it in and retain it"
  69,13,And when (the Last Hour comes and) the Trumpet is blown with a single blast
  69,14,"And the earth, and the mountains (on it) are removed and burst within, and are crushed with a single crushing"
  69,15,It is on that Day that the Event to happen will happen
  69,16,"And the sky split asunder, and so, on that Day it will be most frail"
  69,17,"And the angels will be at its ends; and above them, eight will bear the Throne of your Lord on that Day"
  69,18,"On that Day you will be arraigned for judgment, and no secret of yours will remain hidden"
  69,19,"Then as for him who is given his Record in his right hand, he will say: \"Here, take and read my Record"
  69,20,I surely knew that (one day) I would meet my account
  69,21,And so he will be in a state of life pleasing to him
  69,22,In a lofty Garden
  69,23,With clusters (of fruit) within easy reach
  69,24,Eat and drink to your hearts’ content for all that you sent ahead in advance in days past (in anticipation of this Day)
  69,25,"But as for him whose Record is given in his left hand, he will say: \"Ah, would that I had never been given my Record"
  69,26,And that I had known nothing of my account
  69,27,"Oh, would that death had been (and nothing thereafter had followed)"
  69,28,My wealth has availed me nothing
  69,29,And all my authority (my power over all that I had) has gone from me
  69,30,"(And the command will come): \"Lay hold of him and shackle him (by the neck, the hands, and the feet)"
  69,31,Then in the Blazing Flame let him to roast
  69,32,"Then, fasten him with a chain the length of which is seventy cubits"
  69,33,"For he surely did not believe in God, the Supreme"
  69,34,And did not urge to the feeding of the destitute
  69,35,"And so, he will have none to befriend him this Day"
  69,36,Nor any food except foul pus
  69,37,None eat it except the sinful (those guilty of denying God or associating partners with Him and oppressing people)
  69,38,No indeed! I swear by all that you can see
  69,39,And all that you cannot see
  69,40,"It surely is the speech (conveyed to you by) an illustrious, noble Messenger"
  69,41,And not a poet’s speech (composed in a poet’s mind). How little is what you believe! (It is so limited by the poverty of your souls and hearts)
  69,42,Nor is it a soothsayer’s speech (pretending to foretell events). How little it is that you reflect and be mindful! (It is so limited by the poverty of your minds)
  69,43,(No indeed!) It is a Revelation being sent down in parts from the Lord of the worlds
  69,44,If he (the Messenger) had dared to fabricate some false sayings in attribution to Us
  69,45,We would certainly have seized him with might
  69,46,Thereafter We would certainly have cut his life-vein
  69,47,Then not one from among you could have shielded and saved him from Us
  69,48,"And it is a sure Reminder (bringing hope and guidance) for the God-revering, pious"
  69,49,We are most certainly aware that among you are some who deny (it)
  69,50,It will surely be a bitter regret for the unbelievers
  69,51,And this (the whole Qur’an) is surely certain truth
  69,52,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Supreme"
  70,1,A questioner (in mocking denial of the Day of Resurrection) has asked about the punishment certain to befall
  70,2,(And prepared for) the unbelievers; none can ward it off (from them)
  70,3,"(It is) from God, Whose are the stairs of ascent"
  70,4,"The angels and the Spirit ascend to Him (thereby), in a day the measure of which is fifty thousand years (of your normal worldly years)"
  70,5,So (O Messenger) endure (their insolence) with becoming patience
  70,6,They see it (the punishment) as far off (beyond their reason and perception)
  70,7,But We see it as (certain to come and) near at hand
  70,8,The Day when the sky will be like molten metal
  70,9,And the mountains will be like multi-colored tufts of wool
  70,10,And no loyal friend will ask after his friend
  70,11,Though they will be in sight of each other. Every disbelieving criminal will yearn to ransom himself from the punishment of that Day even by his sons
  70,12,And his wife and his brother
  70,13,And all his kinsfolk who sheltered him
  70,14,"And whoever else is on the earth, all of them, so that he might then save himself"
  70,15,By no means! It is a furiously flaming fire
  70,16,Tearing away the skin
  70,17,It will call to itself those who turn their backs (on the call to faith) and turn away (from worship of God)
  70,18,And amass wealth and withhold it (from spending in God’s cause and for the needy)